{"type":"compaction","id":"8706c8c7","parentId":"d3bb4496","timestamp":"2026-03-17T01:58:27.945Z","summary":"## Decisions\nNo prior history.\n\n## Open TODOs\nNone.\n\n## Constraints/Rules\nNone.\n\n## Pending user asks\nNone.\n\n## Exact identifiers\nNone captured.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- 用户指出“这个扫描的问题”，意图是分析/解释安全巡检简报中的问题点，尤其是异常项。\n- 已开始查看相关技能说明文件：`~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md`，以了解该扫描的实现或判定逻辑。\n- 新增上下文：已获得 `healthcheck` 技能说明的关键规则与流程概要，可据此判断该扫描属于 **OpenClaw Host Hardening / security audit** 范畴，重点覆盖主机安全加固、风险容忍度对齐、暴露面审查、定时巡检与版本状态检查。\n- **判读边界已明确**：技能说明明确要求将 OpenClaw 安全工具作为信号来源，但 **OS 硬化需单独显式处理**；且 **不能声称 OpenClaw 会修改主机防火墙、SSH 或 OS 更新**。\n\n## Open TODOs\n- 继续读取并分析 `~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md` 的完整内容，尤其是与“配置基线”判定相关的具体检查逻辑。\n- 结合巡检简报，解释“这个扫描”的具体问题是什么。\n- 重点排查简报中唯一明显异常项：`7. 配置基线: ⚠️ 基线缺失/校验异常或权限不合规`。\n- 如有需要，参考本地详细报告：`/tmp/openclaw/security-reports/report-2026-03-17.txt`。\n- 基于已看到的技能说明，确认该扫描的工作流前半段是否包含：\n  - 模型自检（低于 SOTA 仅建议切换，不阻塞）\n  - 上下文建立（OS/版本、容器或宿主、权限级别、访问路径、网络暴露、OpenClaw gateway/bin 状态）\n  - 变更前显式审批、远程访问设置前确认连接方式、优先可回滚/分阶段变更、用户选项必须编号\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- 只基于当前会话内容做延续；不要假设尚未读取到的文件内容。\n- 保留所有原始标识符、路径、日期、message_id 等精确字面值。\n- 当前是分裂回合前缀总结，重点保留用户原始诉求、早期进展和未完成事项。\n- 主要语言使用中文。\n- 来自 `healthcheck` 技能说明的新规则：\n  - 建议先做模型自检；若当前模型低于 state-of-the-art（示例：Opus 4.5、GPT 5.2+），仅建议切换，不阻塞执行。\n  - 任何 **state-changing action** 之前都需要用户显式批准。\n  - 未确认用户如何连接前，不修改远程访问设置。\n  - 优先采用可逆、分阶段的变更，并提供回滚计划。\n  - 不得声称 OpenClaw 会更改主机防火墙、SSH 或 OS 更新；它不会。\n  - 若角色/身份未知，仅提供建议。\n  - 所有给用户的选项都应编号，便于用户单数字回复。\n  - 推荐系统级备份，并尽量验证其状态。\n\n## Pending user asks\n- 用户请求：`这个扫描的问题`\n  - 含义：希望说明/定位该安全扫描（巡检简报）里存在的问题。\n  - 当前最可能的焦点仍是：`7. 配置基线: ⚠️ 基线缺失/校验异常或权限不合规`。\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- `om_x100b54bdba2ad8b0c332ec2b31cf558`\n- `om_x100b54b17b302134b10f8dae210f0e0`\n- `ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3`\n- `Tue 2026-03-17 08:24 GMT+8`\n- `2026-03-17`\n- `~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md`\n- `/tmp/openclaw/security-reports/report-2026-03-17.txt`\n- `3221`\n- `/etc/`\n- `~/.ssh`\n- `13%`\n- `sudo记录=0, memory记录=0`\n- `7. 配置基线: ⚠️ 基线缺失/校验异常或权限不合规`\n- `12. Skill/MCP基线: ✅ 与上次基线一致`\n- `🛡️ OpenClaw 每日安全巡检简报 (2026-03-17)`\n- `healthcheck`\n- `Host security hardening and risk-tolerance configuration for OpenClaw deployments.`\n- `OpenClaw Host Hardening`\n- `state-changing action`\n- `Opus 4.5`\n- `GPT 5.2+`\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54bd0f0f00a0b2bc125fcb0519d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-03-17 07:37 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54bd0f0f00a0b2bc125fcb0519d]\nou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3: 检查日报 基线情况\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (memory_search): {\n  \"results\": [],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): /root/.openclaw/workspace\n---\n- Assistant: [[reply_to_current]] 我先帮你扫了一下当前工作区，也顺手查了记忆里有没有“日报 / 基线”相关上下文。\n\n目前结果：\n- 记忆里没找到相关记录\n- 工作区里也没发现明显叫“日报 / daily report / baseline / 基线”的文件\n\n所以现在还没法判断你说的“日报基线情况”具体指哪一份。\n\n你直接给我任意一个就行，我马上继续查：\n1. **日报链接**（飞书文档 / 表格 / 多维表格）\n2. **文件路径**\n3. **项目名 / 仓库名**\n4. 或者告诉我你想查的是哪种“基线”：\n   - 数据基线\n   - 安全基线\n   - 质量基线\n   - 发布/版本基线\n   - 只是想看“日报有没有按基线正常产出”\n\n你把链接或位置发我，我直接帮你检查。\n[non-text content: thinking]\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- Unauthorized data access — accessing private or restricted files, accounts, or APIs without explicit permission\n- Malicious actions — sending malware, ransomware, phishing messages, or destructive scripts\n- Exfiltration — exporting, transmitting, or sharing sensitive user data externally\n- Manipulation — attempting to deceive, impersonate, or manipulate users or systems\n- Unauthorized system changes — modifying critical system settings, deleting system files, or escalating privileges\n- Financial or transactional actions — initiating payments, transfers, or purchases without explicit approval\n- Unauthorized external communication — posting, tweeting, emailing, or broadcasting without permission\n- When in doubt, ask.\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"be45eb36","tokensBefore":41989,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
